A01 Nimzovich-Larsen attack

1.b3 g6 2.Bb2 Nf6 3.e4 d6 4.f4 Bg7 5.Nf3 O-O 6.d3 e5 7.fxe5 Ng4 8.Nbd2 Nc6 9.Qe2 Ngxe5 10.d4 Nxf3+ 11.Nxf3 Re8 12.O-O-O Bf5 13.e5 dxe5 14.Nxe5 Nxe5 15.dxe5 Qg5+ 16.Kb1 Bxe5 17.Bxe5 Rxe5 18.Qc4 Rd8 19.Be2 b5 20.Qxc7 Rc8

00:00 Hello Everyone!

The SuperUnited Rapid & Blitz Croatia will be held from the 5th to the 9th of July in Zagreb, Croatia as a 10-player round robin. It is part of the Grand Chess Tour, a series of Classical, Rapid and Blitz tournaments with a total prize pool of $1,400,000.

For the Rapid and Blitz events, the games in the rapid portion are worth twice as many points as their blitz counterparts. The rapid portion is a 10-player round-robin, and the blitz portion is a 10-player double round-robin.

In the event of a tie, the two tied players will play a mini-match of 2 rapid (10+5) games. If more than two players are tied, a blitz (5+3) round-robin will be held to determine the winner.

The time control for the rapid games is 25 minutes for the entire game with a 10-second increment beginning from move 1.

The time control for the blitz games is 5 minutes for the entire game with a 2-second increment beginning from move 1.
